[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Pekko Tests**\n\nI’m looking into the existing tests for `org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor` and noting that just adding `pekko-actor-typed` won’t help with failing tests since it doesn't restore classic TypedActor classes. Coverage for pekko-actor can involve using ActorSystem and other elements without needing Docker or specific environments. I wonder if the tests need system properties set for DnsSettings, especially considering past configurations that required special JVM exports. I might need to dig into the documentation for more clarity.\n\n**Analyzing Scala Build Dependencies**\n\nI'm investigating the existing build, which includes the Scala compiler due to the Scala tests. It seems the generated scaffold likely has dependencies like target, assertj, and JUnit. I’m curious if the Scala artifact requires both the scala-library and compiler. Also, is the driver test scaffold necessary specifically for Scala? From what I can see, the existing build already includes both the scala-library and compiler, but I want to clarify their roles in the project.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c8ad68683493f73016a40d985ad8c819496ea4ef674d95439\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQNmPUuqkS5P1_V-e1pXLr863agUsZH7VVoJIugTT47Dt2U3MkYs4DrKqOOzBbX5GdsoTiSrdzRpmL70tbKrd85ndwNZTyh-QLtflS2mRfPZI9mU67yYtxStZo0I9wwxGVBYJVrqWb8dLjPltXEcp7vtyu_uJ9HXqtPzP8CmO_GY_KbWlzvPt00vbnZC68gAStkZ4AZp5NDwsPAtkhRdVwvtJyAH3A0iOZN2B25lsej2WXVAaE55_ub-jI6feGGzq-cmjux157w4AsZITz7tzd26kxU59sZwHt3H29r6IuHyUW4PWJoxXOYGy6DuEOMtWPJ3a5g55-NEcJ_pvCBKOiXAg0z0_PvIg_RWRVzoW0bskcs7HnqPPcLlTcS_yoAwrjSH2kxLvyd7HQ_rCkX8x-Dr4pkV2ugzspwPWcMEKYHlk6baPEQlrDrA0v_kdBSq_DjaVx6YiFfw6HKIt3JuuFqgYWCOkoWTcIy6MaBCe8FYQKSLOqfjkqXRzUAHw32-KbIr8Q9yiG3HuZMuTdOSCT9UpL-6RzUbOEVS5GsasIcN_jww4AMuvEi_gNfWJet37m3ppoegs5YIfDr6h21uGfXS3e_YJqbFfdrtjwDwaPlcfPCV2bKK14RmHfEbHDn8_AJM